01:36.397 --> 01:38.298
It's amazing arriving here

01:38.299 --> 01:41.100
after all you see on TV these

01:41.101 --> 01:45.672
days that Libya is, in
fact, functioning at all.

01:45.673 --> 01:46.839
But it is.

01:46.840 --> 01:53.546
The fountains across from
the kornish are operating.

01:53.547 --> 01:54.847
Traffic works, kind of.

01:54.848 --> 01:57.850
At the Rattison, club sandwiches

01:57.851 --> 01:58.985
arrive on time in the lobby.

01:58.986 --> 02:00.653
The occasional flash of camo and

02:00.654 --> 02:03.122
a security scanner are the

02:03.123 --> 02:05.492
really only discordant notes.

02:05.493 --> 02:12.899
Don't want to take the...
Inside the old part of the

02:12.900 --> 02:15.502
city, men slaughter a camel,

02:15.503 --> 02:23.503
while a girl records
it with her iPad.

02:24.278 --> 02:25.378
Okay.

02:25.379 --> 02:25.813
He said no.

02:25.814 --> 02:30.082
Kids are setting off
fireworks in the Medina.

02:30.083 --> 02:35.788
Incoming.

02:35.789 --> 02:39.692
Tomorrow is the prophet

02:39.693 --> 02:40.328
Muhammad's birthday, and people

02:40.328 --> 02:40.961
who have not known freedom for

02:40.962 --> 02:48.962
nearly 50 years are
ready to celebrate.

02:52.506 --> 02:54.974
The square is filled with

02:54.975 --> 02:59.479
families, kids, teenage
skater boys and hot shots on

02:59.480 --> 02:59.780
motorcycles.

02:59.781 --> 03:05.184
It's wild.

03:05.185 --> 03:11.958
An almost giddily happy.

03:11.959 --> 03:14.160
Young men in the camouflage

03:14.161 --> 03:16.929
pants of the militias, most of

03:16.930 --> 03:19.866
whom were civilians until
last year, do their best to

03:19.867 --> 03:27.867
sporadically keep order
or just join in the fun.

03:30.244 --> 03:32.512
Every kid above the age of 5

03:32.513 --> 03:39.786
seems to have been issued a
lighter and a fistful of

03:39.787 --> 03:40.721
fireworks.

03:40.722 --> 03:45.157
Ambulances idle on the margins
of the square to treat

03:45.158 --> 03:53.158
fireworks-related injuries,
which there will be many.

04:12.320 --> 04:13.886
This is Tripoli.

04:13.887 --> 04:19.892
After 42 years of nightmare.

04:19.892 --> 04:22.060
How to build a whole society

04:22.062 --> 04:24.664
overnight and make it work in

04:24.665 --> 04:25.633
one of the most contentious and

04:25.634 --> 04:27.266
difficult areas of the world is

04:27.267 --> 04:35.267
what people are
trying to figure out.

04:46.053 --> 04:51.758
♪

04:51.759 --> 04:53.860
So before the war, did you

04:53.861 --> 04:56.563
think it would ever be possible,

04:56.564 --> 04:58.230
did you dream some day
this will change?

04:58.231 --> 05:01.534
No.

05:01.535 --> 05:06.138
In Gaddafi's country,
you can't say a word.

05:06.139 --> 05:07.139
You'd get killed.

05:07.140 --> 05:07.808
It was impossible.

05:07.809 --> 05:10.577
Then I joined the
group, you know?

05:10.578 --> 05:11.811
The militia.

05:11.812 --> 05:15.515
Omar is young and was even
younger when the fighting

05:15.516 --> 05:15.749
started.

05:15.750 --> 05:17.049
He like so many Libyans from

05:17.050 --> 05:18.551
around the country and many who

05:18.552 --> 05:20.520
had left heeded the calls for

05:20.521 --> 05:22.755
revolution on
Facebook and Twitter.

05:22.756 --> 05:28.361
They fog in Tripoli, Benghazi,

05:28.362 --> 05:30.229
Mizrada and everywhere
in between.

05:30.230 --> 05:30.998
Who won this war?

05:30.998 --> 05:31.832
Young people or everybody?

05:31.833 --> 05:35.802
Everybody.

05:35.803 --> 05:41.441
But the young people... what
was your life like as a

05:41.442 --> 05:42.575
revolutionary?

05:42.576 --> 05:45.445
You do this for the next
generation, for a better

05:45.446 --> 05:46.479
country, a better life.

05:46.480 --> 05:54.480
You have a future now.

05:55.055 --> 06:01.227
There was no future in Libya
before Gaddafi's regime.

06:01.228 --> 06:03.295
A seafood restaurant on
the Mediterranean coast.

06:03.296 --> 06:06.799
One of the best foods in
Libya, I think, the seafood.

06:06.800 --> 06:09.268
The menu is not
printed on paper.

06:09.269 --> 06:12.304
It's laid out right
there for you on ice.

06:12.305 --> 06:14.206
We have... what do they do?

06:14.207 --> 06:15.175
They just grill that?

06:15.176 --> 06:16.308
Yeah, they grill it.

06:16.309 --> 06:18.745
Some garlic, some sauce.

06:18.746 --> 06:20.046
You pick out the stuff that

06:20.047 --> 06:23.750
interests you from
the daily catch.

06:23.751 --> 06:23.951
Okay.

06:23.951 --> 06:24.752
Let's get one of these.

06:24.752 --> 06:25.686
One of these.

06:25.687 --> 06:29.889
Some shrimps.

06:29.890 --> 06:30.591
Ca calimari, too.

06:30.592 --> 06:32.992
They cook it for you
the way you want.

06:32.993 --> 06:39.131
Oh, beautiful.

06:39.132 --> 06:39.299
Wow.

06:39.299 --> 06:39.733
That's delicious.

06:39.734 --> 06:46.506
This is the stuffed
calimari, Libyan style.

06:46.507 --> 06:48.641
So many seafood
stuffed inside of it.

06:48.642 --> 06:49.809
Like a Turkey.

06:49.810 --> 06:52.645
Good sauce.

06:52.646 --> 06:53.913
Man, we are living large today.

06:53.914 --> 06:59.218
Yes, we are.

06:59.219 --> 07:01.754
So what were you doing
before the war?

07:01.755 --> 07:03.055
I was a travel agent.

07:03.056 --> 07:07.326
You were a travel agent?

07:07.327 --> 07:08.028
Yes.

07:08.029 --> 07:09.896
And I was studying,
too, medical school.

07:09.897 --> 07:12.364
Many of the people who
started the revolution who

07:12.365 --> 07:20.365
fought in the streets with
makeshift weapons were like

07:23.310 --> 07:23.511
Omar.

07:23.511 --> 07:24.144
They transformed themselves in a

07:24.144 --> 07:24.712
matter of months from kids

07:24.713 --> 07:27.146
playing PlayStation
to hardened fighters.

07:27.147 --> 07:31.450
Nobody believed that he
can be removed, really.

07:31.451 --> 07:33.853
How quickly after the uprising
started did you begin

07:33.854 --> 07:35.655
to think that, wow,
this is possible?

07:35.656 --> 07:38.491
That we might actually win?

07:38.492 --> 07:39.626
The first day.

07:39.627 --> 07:40.427
First day?

07:40.428 --> 07:43.696
Yeah.

07:43.697 --> 07:45.097
The day before, you figured,

07:45.098 --> 07:45.866
impossible, we'll be stuck with

07:45.867 --> 07:48.100
this son of a bitch forever.

07:48.101 --> 07:51.938
A few hours later it's like,
wow, this might work.

07:51.939 --> 07:55.341
Seeing groups with you going

07:55.342 --> 07:56.976
toward the martyrs square,

07:56.977 --> 07:58.444
demanding their rights, at that

07:58.445 --> 08:02.982
moment you feel that
you can do anything.

08:02.983 --> 08:07.987
That this is going to happen.

08:07.988 --> 08:15.988
If it didn't, we'll
die trying to do it.

08:18.666 --> 08:21.333
♪

08:21.334 --> 08:24.236
So much has changed around town.

08:24.237 --> 08:26.238
So much is changing.

08:26.239 --> 08:28.675
New music, graffiti.

08:28.676 --> 08:36.676
These things, they
mean something.

08:39.352 --> 08:45.558
♪

08:45.559 --> 08:46.959
But centuries of strict social

08:46.960 --> 08:48.561
and religious values keep some

08:48.562 --> 08:51.864
things solidly the same.

08:51.865 --> 08:55.635
Alcohol, for instance,
is strictly forbidden.

08:55.636 --> 08:59.238
Men and women follow
hierarchal roles as before.

08:59.239 --> 09:02.241
Since the revolution, there's a

09:02.242 --> 09:09.315
tug-of-war over
what is acceptable.

09:09.316 --> 09:11.984
♪

09:11.985 --> 09:13.886
Outside a mosque in the Medina,

09:13.887 --> 09:19.626
men fill the narrow street to

09:19.627 --> 09:27.627
celebrate Muhammad's birthday.

09:29.036 --> 09:36.609
Snacks are passed around.

09:36.610 --> 09:42.882
Women watch and record
from the rooftops.

09:42.883 --> 09:50.883
♪

09:56.463 --> 10:01.334
♪

10:10.878 --> 10:14.080
There aren't a lot of
conflicts in the world where

10:14.081 --> 10:15.514
there's a clear bad guy.

10:15.515 --> 10:16.649
Clearly there's a bad guy here.

10:16.650 --> 10:17.317
Exactly.

10:17.318 --> 10:19.018
The one thing about Gaddafi is

10:19.019 --> 10:21.954
he believed he was the most

10:21.955 --> 10:23.489
important human being
almost that ever existed.

10:23.490 --> 10:26.726
I mean, he changed the
names of the months.

10:26.727 --> 10:31.731
He changed the date of
the Islamic calendar.

10:31.732 --> 10:35.401
Such megalomania.

10:35.402 --> 10:36.769
Anyone outside, if you mentioned

10:36.770 --> 10:40.072
the name Libya, anyone
would say Gaddafi.

10:40.073 --> 10:43.676
Gaddafi stole the
Liberty of Libya.

10:43.677 --> 10:45.011
Michele cousins is the

10:45.012 --> 10:47.680
co-founder of "the Libya herald"

10:47.681 --> 10:49.181
and has known several different

10:49.182 --> 10:50.516
Libyas in his lifetime.

10:50.517 --> 10:53.285
For so long the news has
been the personality.

10:53.286 --> 10:56.288
Gaddafi turned up to
open a shopping center.

10:56.289 --> 11:00.126
Gaddafi turned up to
open an envelope.

11:00.127 --> 11:01.527
Those of us who knew Libya, knew

11:01.528 --> 11:03.763
there was another Libya,
wonderful people.

11:03.764 --> 11:08.400
We'd talk about it as you
talk about a dead person.

11:08.401 --> 11:08.869
Do you remember this?

11:08.869 --> 11:09.369
Do you remember that?

11:09.370 --> 11:11.403
Then in February 2011, suddenly

11:11.404 --> 11:12.504
there was resurrection.

11:12.505 --> 11:15.374
The dead came back to life.

11:15.375 --> 11:20.346
We meet at a Libyan coffeehouse.

11:20.347 --> 11:24.416
A traditional male
only sort of a joint.

11:24.417 --> 11:26.452
Cafe culture is big here.

11:26.453 --> 11:30.156
A holdover from the days of
Italian colonization when

11:30.157 --> 11:33.860
Mussolini tried to rebuild
Rome's long lost empire.

11:33.861 --> 11:36.896
It's just been the most
amazing experience.

11:36.897 --> 11:39.498
Seeing the rebirth of a
country, of a people.

11:39.499 --> 11:41.834
I mean, last night's fireworks.

11:41.835 --> 11:43.736
There was a general sense of

11:43.737 --> 11:45.404
exuberance bordering on anarchy.

11:45.405 --> 11:48.775
I mean, I felt very
happy there last night.

11:48.776 --> 11:51.443
If somewhat in peril.

11:51.444 --> 11:52.611
It's Christmas.

11:52.612 --> 11:56.548
It's whatever, it's
the fourth of July.

11:56.549 --> 11:57.384
Rolled into one.

11:57.385 --> 12:00.319
Also there are people who
are trying to stop it.

12:00.320 --> 12:03.122
Those puritans, extremists, if

12:03.123 --> 12:05.191
you want to say militants.

12:05.192 --> 12:06.492
What has happened, people have

12:06.493 --> 12:08.761
come out in defiance of that.

12:08.762 --> 12:10.596
They're showing, we
want to have fun.

12:10.597 --> 12:13.732
For a long time in Libya,
you couldn't have fun.

12:13.733 --> 12:15.802
The biggest misconception is
the place is turning into

12:15.803 --> 12:16.936
another Afghanistan and Iraq

12:16.937 --> 12:18.704
where you have bombs
go off, attacks.

12:18.705 --> 12:20.706
But it's not, as you've seen.

12:20.707 --> 12:22.508
Libyans have gone through an

12:22.509 --> 12:24.410
awful time having
fought for freedom.

12:24.411 --> 12:25.812
People have died.

12:25.813 --> 12:26.913
People have struggled.

12:26.914 --> 12:33.954
And that's going to
hold them together.

12:47.835 --> 12:55.707
Kids are selling fireworks
across from the arch.

12:55.708 --> 12:58.344
One is constantly reminded that

12:58.345 --> 12:59.778
Libya was once a vital part of

12:59.779 --> 13:02.281
the ancient Roman empire.

13:02.282 --> 13:05.684
That was nearly 2,000 years ago.

13:05.685 --> 13:06.853
Tonight I was told was going to

13:06.854 --> 13:09.555
be an even bigger, Wilder

13:09.556 --> 13:13.059
celebration in martyrs square.

13:13.060 --> 13:17.163
But something has happened
since last night.

13:17.164 --> 13:18.931
The British foreign office has

13:18.932 --> 13:22.001
just told all UK citizens
to leave Benghazi.

13:22.002 --> 13:23.435
Libya's second largest city.

13:23.436 --> 13:29.675
Due to an unspecified threat.

13:29.676 --> 13:31.177
The Libyan government, such as

13:31.178 --> 13:36.515
it is, has denied any basis
for such drastic action.

13:36.516 --> 13:41.787
A lone cherry bomb now and
again, an awkward flurry of

13:41.788 --> 13:42.755
Roman candles.

13:42.756 --> 13:47.426
The buzz of last night's chaotic

13:47.427 --> 13:49.996
party parched, big time.

13:49.997 --> 13:51.197
Whether or not this is the

13:51.198 --> 13:52.698
larger geopolitical decision,

13:52.699 --> 13:54.233
the vibe toward this western

13:54.234 --> 13:56.969
film crew seems apprehensive.

13:56.970 --> 14:04.970
Uncertain.

14:08.015 --> 14:10.116
The following day feels better.

14:10.117 --> 14:14.921
Somewhat.

14:14.922 --> 14:21.928
Fresh produce is for
sale on Tripoli streets.

14:21.929 --> 14:24.063
If you were a small restaurant,

14:24.064 --> 14:25.731
or shopping for a big family,

14:25.732 --> 14:27.866
you'd bring cash, a wheelbarrow,

14:27.867 --> 14:31.938
and load up on what you need.

14:31.939 --> 14:36.175
But the revolution has
brought changed tastes.

14:36.176 --> 14:37.910
Libyans, especially young

14:37.911 --> 14:45.911
Libyans, hunger for
more than just freedom.

14:45.953 --> 14:51.490
They hunger for
places like this.

14:51.491 --> 14:52.491
Kentucky fried chi

14:55.628 --> 14:55.895
chicken.

14:55.896 --> 14:59.165
The colonel, his buddies, the

14:59.166 --> 15:00.399
king and the crown have not made

15:00.400 --> 15:03.669
it here given the uncertainty
of the situation.

15:03.670 --> 15:04.836
In the meantime, places like

15:04.837 --> 15:05.871
this have been popping up.

15:05.872 --> 15:06.306
Uncle Kentucky.

15:06.307 --> 15:13.679
Awesome.

15:13.680 --> 15:15.181
You know where Kentucky is?

15:15.182 --> 15:17.183
Kentucky is from USA.

15:17.184 --> 15:17.884
A part.

15:17.884 --> 15:18.418
Yeah.

15:18.419 --> 15:20.219
This place is new?

15:20.220 --> 15:24.590
Yeah.

15:24.591 --> 15:24.857
It's new.

15:24.858 --> 15:27.226
Before Gaddafi... not possible.

15:27.227 --> 15:27.660
Now it's normal.

15:27.661 --> 15:32.398
Oh, that's nice.

15:32.399 --> 15:33.799
How you found it?

15:33.800 --> 15:37.469
Spicy, delicious.

15:37.470 --> 15:42.274
Johar, like many Libyans his
age, fought to overthrow

15:42.275 --> 15:42.509
Gaddafi.

15:42.510 --> 15:43.709
He was there, gun in hand, when

15:43.710 --> 15:48.380
they stormed Gaddafi's
palace compound.

15:48.381 --> 15:49.781
Happy, excited?

15:49.782 --> 15:52.451
Nice feeling.

15:52.452 --> 16:00.452
Nice feeling that Gaddafi
he killed my cousin.

16:05.032 --> 16:07.499
I don't want anyone
to die in war.

16:07.500 --> 16:09.235
He's killed for nothing.

16:09.236 --> 16:16.642
The first thing I think
that killing people is bad.

16:16.643 --> 16:18.244
He's leave me do that.

16:18.245 --> 16:21.113
Because if I don't kill
him, he kills any.

16:21.114 --> 16:22.148
It's nice to see freedom.

16:22.149 --> 16:23.815
It's nice to see
the bad guy done.

16:23.816 --> 16:24.317
It's nice.

16:24.318 --> 16:25.884
I feel welcome here.

16:25.885 --> 16:27.253
Finally.

16:27.254 --> 16:30.589
We say no on him.

16:30.590 --> 16:32.458
He's now died.

16:32.459 --> 16:35.661
That's what we wanted.

16:35.662 --> 16:39.131
To Johar, a few pieces of

16:39.132 --> 16:41.900
greasy fried chicken eaten in a

16:41.901 --> 16:49.901
brightly colored fast food
setting means more.

16:52.245 --> 16:53.412
My country.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.147
I want the feeling of
the taste of freedom.

16:55.148 --> 16:57.616
The taste of freedom.

16:57.617 --> 17:04.256
It's a nice taste.

17:04.257 --> 17:09.295
♪

17:09.296 --> 17:12.897
Good.

17:12.898 --> 17:20.640
Good food.

17:24.310 --> 17:32.311
Outside Tripoli's
center, there's this.

17:32.652 --> 17:37.022
One time axis of all
power and untold evil.

17:37.023 --> 17:41.460
Sinister offices, barracks,

17:41.461 --> 17:47.266
residences, on top of secret
tunnels and underground

17:47.267 --> 17:48.767
facilities.

17:48.768 --> 17:56.768
Gaddafi's enormous compound.

17:57.710 --> 18:00.011
Most everything belonging to or

18:00.012 --> 18:08.012
associated with Gaddafi
was destroyed.

18:15.094 --> 18:19.598
On August 3rd, 2011,
it fell to rebels.

18:19.599 --> 18:25.337
Gaddafi and his
family having fled.

18:25.338 --> 18:31.277
This is what's left
of Gaddafi's palace.

18:31.278 --> 18:37.384
♪

18:46.659 --> 18:54.659
♪

18:55.402 --> 18:58.804
So when's the last
time you were here?

18:58.805 --> 19:03.775
Last time is when the
revolution is finishing.

19:03.776 --> 19:09.815
The machinery, going in fast.

19:09.816 --> 19:13.252
After then, coming
a lot of people.

19:13.253 --> 19:14.920
Listening about something
expensive here.

19:14.921 --> 19:15.422
Pardon?

19:15.423 --> 19:17.122
Like the salt.

19:17.123 --> 19:17.990
What?

19:17.991 --> 19:20.526
He wants us to stop
filming right now.

19:20.527 --> 19:20.827
Okay.

19:20.828 --> 19:22.761
While talking, we didn't notice

19:22.762 --> 19:24.696
several pickup trucks of local

19:24.697 --> 19:28.166
militia had closed in on us.

19:28.167 --> 19:29.035
Stop.

19:29.035 --> 19:29.236
Stop.

19:29.237 --> 19:30.536
I'll stop.

19:30.537 --> 19:31.837
Just relax.

19:31.838 --> 19:32.038
Relax.

19:32.038 --> 19:32.305
Relax.

19:32.306 --> 19:34.105
Relax.

19:34.106 --> 19:36.608
This is their turf, or their

19:36.609 --> 19:39.945
area of operation or somehow
under their control.

19:39.946 --> 19:47.052
Whatever the case, they're
the group in charge today.

19:47.053 --> 19:54.326
An argument ensues between
our guys and their guys.

19:54.327 --> 19:55.561
All of whom fought against the

19:55.562 --> 20:02.902
same forces on this
ground a year ago.

20:11.344 --> 20:11.578
Okay.

20:11.579 --> 20:19.579
Let's go.

